<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><listPerson xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><person xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="BOD02" sex="1"><persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><roleName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/><forename xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Samuel</forename><surname xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Boddington</surname><addName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></persName><birth xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1766-06-19"><placeName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></birth><death xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1843-04-19"/><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">West Indies Merchant and Irish Politician</occupation><note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="editorial"><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Married to Grace Ashburner, whom he met 
    at <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="MOR03">George Cadogan Morgan's</persName> home; she later eloped with his cousin 
    Benjamin Boddington.  After Grace's departure, their children lived for a time with the Morgans.</p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">The Boddington family held large estates in the West Indies and Samuel had been left a fortune 
     by his father who had been a director of the South Sea Company as well as a West India merchant 
     with offices at Mark Lane.  After his wife left, Samuel approached his friend, <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="SHA02">Richard Sharp</persName> (politician), 
     a fellow Dissenter, fellow member of the Fishmongers' Company, and both mutual 
     friends of <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="ROG01">Samuel Rogers</persName>, asking if he would join him in business, 
    and eventually a West India company of Boddington, Sharp and Philips (George Philips) was established 
    at 17 Mark Lane. Both Boddington and Philips (later Sir George Philips) followed Sharp's example and became dissenting Whig members of Parliament. 
  Boddington was Member of Parliament (MP) for Tralee from January to May 1807.</p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">There is a question about the relationship between <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="BOD01">John Boddington</persName> and Samuel.  Occasions linked to Amelia Alderson have been coded for John; occasions 
  linked to Morgan, Sharp and Rogers have been linked to Samuel.</p></note><bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="other"><title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></bibl><bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="printedbook">Mary Ann Constantine and Paul Frame (eds) <title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">A World of New Ideas: The Travels 
